ass=\"cl-881e0d7a\"><p class=\"cl-881defc0\"><span class=\"cl-881a6d50\">0.760</span></p></td><td class=\"cl-881e0d7a\"><p class=\"cl-881defc0\"><span class=\"cl-881a6d50\">0.241</span></p></td><td class=\"cl-881e0d7a\"><p class=\"cl-881defc0\"><span class=\"cl-881a6d50\">0.006</span></p></td><td class=\"cl-881e0d7a\"><p class=\"cl-881defc0\"><span class=\"cl-881a6d50\">0.011</span></p></td><td class=\"cl-881e0d7a\"><p class=\"cl-881defc0\"><span class=\"cl-881a6d50\">0.018</span></p></td><td class=\"cl-881e0d7a\"><p class=\"cl-881defc0\"><span class=\"cl-881a6d50\">0.198</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n\\elandscape\n\n\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n\n## ReGenesees\n\nReGenesees (R Evolved Generalized Software for Sampling Estimates and Errors in Surveys) is een R-pakket voor het uitvoeren van design-based en model-assisted analyses van complexe steekproeven. Het ondersteunt multistage, gestratificeerde, geclusterde en ongelijk gewogen steekproefontwerpen. Voor niet-lineaire (gladde) schatters wordt de steekproefvariantie geschat met behulp van Taylor-reeks linearisatie.\n\nDe volgende stappen werden uitgevoerd: \n\n- Elke predictie werd gekoppeld aan de totale oppervlakte er beschikbaar is van dat clustering niveau en de frequentie van de voorkomende clustering niveaus. \n- de Inverse Probability Sampling (IPS) werd bepaald per clustering niveau door zijn frequentie te delen door zijn oppervlakte. De inverse hiervan wordt beschouwd als een gewicht voor de sampling units. \n- Aan elke observatie werd een bepaalde naam gegeven (ids)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n[1] 7046298\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n[1] 0\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n[1] -5707278\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n# Data frame of known totals for a *global* calibration task\n- Number of rows:         1\n- Number of columns:      6\n- Number of known totals: 6\n\n# The data frame structure is as follows\n## Columns 1-6 identify known totals organized into *1 BLOCK* \n\n - BLOCK 1 ---------------------------------------------------------------- \n - Benchmark:           Counts of map \n - Known totals:        6 \n - Auxiliary variables: 6 \n - Columns:             1-6 \n\n    1                               2                           \naux \"Fully Dynamic (All Different)\" \"Reverted (1 LU in between)\"\n    3                             4                    5                       \naux \"Reverted (2 LUs in between)\" \"Shifted (1 Change)\" \"Shifted (2 LU Changes)\"\n    6                   \naux \"Stable (No Change)\"\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n\n# Checking Known Totals dataframe: OK\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\nCalibrated, Stratified 1 - Stage Cluster Sampling Design\n- [6] strata\n- [1822] clusters\n\nCall:\nReGenesees::e.calibrate(design = design, df.population = df.pop, \n    calmodel = ~map - 1)\n\nWeights:\n   Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. \n  121.1   136.7   136.7   152.2   170.2   403.7 \n\nSample stratum sizes: \n     Fully Dynamic (All Different) Reverted (1 LU in between)\nObs                            147                        640\nPSUs                            49                        128\n     Reverted (2 LUs in between) Shifted (1 Change) Shifted (2 LU Changes)\nObs                           52               3720                   2052\nPSUs                          13                744                    342\n     Stable (No Change)\nObs                2184\nPSUs                546\n\nPopulation stratum sizes: \n     Stable (No Change) Shifted (1 Change) Reverted (1 LU in between)\nPSUs           264469.5           508538.9                   138127.1\n     Shifted (2 LU Changes) Fully Dynamic (All Different)\nPSUs               349213.5                       59339.7\n     Reverted (2 LUs in between)\nPSUs                     19331.8\n\nData variables:\n [1] \"map\"          \"ref\"          \"area_m2.x\"    \"area_ha\"      \"area_m2.y\"   \n [6] \"n\"            \"ips\"          \"weights\"      \"ids\"          \"ones\"        \n[11] \"oa\"           \"n_ref\"        \"prop_area_ha\" \"weights.cal\" \n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n    g.min     g.max \n0.1666667 0.3333333 \n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\nAll Calibration Constraints (6) fulfilled (at tolerance level epsilon = 1e-07).\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n   Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. \n  121.1   136.7   136.7   152.2   170.2   403.7 \n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n       Total           SE\nones 1339020 1.673213e-09\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n✔ No differences\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n`old`: 10231.8 15214.0 8133.5 22497.0 21597.9 16417.0\n`new`: 10227.2 15205.8 8130.1 22483.6 21586.4 16406.8\n```\n\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n✔ No differences\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n`old`: 0.010423\n`new`: 0.010417\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n✔ No differences\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n`old`: 0.071 0.042 0.138 0.014 0.025 0.011\n`new`: 0.072 0.042 0.144 0.014 0.025 0.011\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](accuracy_files/figure-html/accuracy_regenesees-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](accuracy_files/figure-html/accuracy_regenesees-2.png){width=672}\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n✔ No differences\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n✔ No differences\n```\n\n\n:::\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\